		<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
			
			<p>Excellent article. The language today has been amped up to Iraq invasion level. Even with issues like the border, where headlines such as &#8220;Biden signs international deal&#8221; to soften the fact that the deal was to increase police south of the border. And now we have the left (of which I once indentefied) calling non supporters of Syrian involvement &#8220;Assad Apologists&#8221; and worse &#8220;Fascists&#8221;. Of course, this is language of people influenced by msm media. Imagine that, people who don&#8217;t support war are now Fascists.</p>
<p>I really appreciate this article. Would love a deep analysis of media language today.</p>
